series.name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic

deck: Steven helps a friend who is afraid of thunderstorms.
name: When It Rains

description:
A group of acrobatic men dressed in black break into the U.S. Mint in Carson City but they don't steal any money, though they kill a guard and cause an explosion.

Jim West and Artemus Gordon are sent to investigate.
name: The Night of Sudden Death

description: When Thanos and the Black Order attack Earth, they finally plan to take over the planet by destroying the Avengers. The Avengers team discovers they are more than eight heroes. The Avengers are an ideal.
name: Avengers World

description:
A Celestial head threatens the Guardians and they storm Korath's ship to rescue Quill, Gamora and the mysterious CryptoCube that holds the Cosmic Seed.

The Guardians have to fight against none other than Knowhere itself as well as having to fend off Korath the Pursuer.
name: Knowhere to Run

description:
Rocket feels under appreciated and accepts an offer to work for the Collector, but soon realizes his "job" is to work as another prisoner in the Collector's collection.

Rocket takes on a job from the Collector.
name: One in a Million You

description: Vixen returns to her birthplace and is confronted with the origin of the Totem as well as finally meeting a member of her family.
name: Episode 5

deck: Gordon and Bullock track down a nemesis from the past.
description: Gordon and Bullock track down a nemesis from the past, leading to a standoff between Jerome and Gordon. Meanwhile, a magic show at the Gotham Children's Hospital gala turns into a hostage situation.
name: The Last Laugh

description: Velmas got an interview at the prestigious Kingston University, the most selective school in the country. The only catch? The dean wants her and the rest of the Scooby gang to figure out why the ghost of Elias Kingston, the schools founder, is haunting Kingstons book-filled halls!
name: Mystery 101

description:
While Bee and his Team try to bring in a gang of Decepticon thieves, Optimus readies himself for a coming evil that will threaten both Earth and Cybertron.

First Airing was in Singapore, US Airing was June 13, 2015
name: Out of Focus

description: When Denny and the Bots are captured, Russell must keep his cool to protect the team from a Decepticon who gives life to the Autobot's worst fears.
name: Even Robots Have Nightmares

description: When the Team's latest quarry leaves Sideswipe powerless, the young Autobot must learn that he can't always rely on his physical prowess.
name: Some Body, Any Body

description: Drift returns to Earth in pursuit of disgruntled runaway Jetstorm - just as the Bee Team must contend with Springload and Quillfire flying the coop.
name: One of Our Mini-Cons Is Missing

description: Unaware that Grimlock is covering up a serious injury, Bee and the Team head to the ocean floor in pursuit of an escaped Decepticon.
name: Deep Trouble

description: When a Decepticon Gladiator and his cheating Manager enter a human Demolition Derby, Grimlock, Denny and Fixit pose as competitors.
name: The Champ

description: An attempt to fix ailing Fixit goes horribly wrong, converting the Mini-Con into a fully weaponized and leathal prison guard who mistakes the Bee Team for Decepitcon fugitives.
name: The Trouble with Fixit

description: After Steeljaw and his Pack commandeer the Scrapyard and it's defenses, our heroes must find a way to take back their base - or face an army to freed Decepticon prisoners.
name: Lockout

description: A restless Grimlock ponders returning to old habits when another Dinobot goes on a rampage.
name: Similarly Different

description: The Bee Team encounters a new Autobot, sent to Earth long ago.
name: The Buzz on Windblade

description: An educational trip turns into a Decepticon hunt as Bee and the Bots stumble upon a chameleon-like Fugitive in a western ghost town.
name: Ghosts and Imposters

description: As Optimus prepares to return to Earth to face the mysterious "Evil" he's prophesied, the Bee Team must prevent Steeljaw's Pack from teleporting that same threat onto Earth.
name: Battlegrounds, Part 1

description: Reunited with Optimus Prime, Bee and his Team must use everything they've learned to stop the annihilation of both Earth and Cybertron.
name: Battlegrounds, Part 2

description: Kermit, trying to spare Fozzie's feelings after he writes a bad sketch for the show accidentally leads Fozzie to quit and pursue a carer in screenwriting. Meanwhile - Ms. Piggy is humiliated when she is pranked live on air by a guest and Gonzo uses Liam Hemsworth's photo on his dating profile, leading to complications.
name: Bear Left Then Bear Write

first_appearance_teams.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

team_credits.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

description:
Fred gets a call for help from Chuck, his daredevil of a best friend, leading the gang on a rescue mission deep in the caverns of an ancient civilization.

When Fred's adventurous best friend sends a call for help, it leads the gang into the dark cavern's of a ancient society.
name: Game of Chicken

description: Liv deals with the aftermath of Major's death, Blaine's cure, and Evan's injuries in the explosion. Meanwhile, she consumes the brain of an old man and takes on his worst traits while trying to figure out who murdered him.
name: Grumpy Old Liv

description: Having reluctantly agreed to share information with Rosalind and the ATCU, Coulson and the team go in search for the Inhuman who is killing off other Inhumans, and May feels that Hunter's mission to take down Ward is getting too personal.
name: Devils You Know

description: Setrakian and Fet battle for possession of the Occido Lumen, and gain a surprising new ally. A massive attack imperils Eph, Nora, and Zack's escape from New York.
name: Night Train

description: Liv (Rose McIver) and Detective Babineax (Malcolm Goodwin) investigate the murder of a hard-partying frat boy whose death shocks everyone. After consuming his brains, Liv attends a fraternity party in an attempt to search for clues, but ends up ruling the beer pong table instead. Still desperate to find the cure, Ravi (Rahul Kohli) takes matters into his own hands and brings Major (Robert Buckley) along for the ride. Meanwhile, Blaine (David Anders) meets with Angus (guest star Robert Knepper), a mysterious person from his past.
name: Zombie Bro

description: As civil unrest continues to grow and the dead take over, Travis and Madison must explore new ways to protect their families in the Season 1 finale.
name: The Good Man

description: "Evos" and humans attempt to join together... but an act of terrorism kills thousands and sets humans against the superpowered among them. One year later, Noah Bennet is drawn back into the fray as a new breed of Heroes emerge.
name: Brave New World

description: Noah bails Quentin out of jail to find out what he knows about the June 13 incident. Meanwhile, Joanne and Luke escape the cell that Tommy sent them to, Brad asks Tommy for a favor, and Miko meets her father in the VR realm.
name: Odessa

description:
Erica Kravid (Rya Khilstedt), the powerful woman behind the global conglomerate Renautas, reveals just how far she will go to protect the world from Evos. Tommy (Robbie Kay) finds comfort in sharing his ability with Emily (Gatlin Green) and a new-found popularity at school. In Japan, Miko's (Kiki Sukezane) rescue mission comes up against some unexpected obstacles. Elsewhere, Noah Bennet (Jack Coleman) continues to work with Quentin (Henry Zeborwski) in his search for the truth and Malina (Danika Yarosh) is guided by an unseen force.

Meanwhile, Luke (Zachary Levi) and Joanne (Judi Shekioni) continue on their deadly mission and Carlos' (Ryan Guzman) search for answers causes him to dig deep to find the hero within.
name: Under the Mask

description:
In search of someone from his past, Noah Bennet (Jack Coleman) breaks in to Renautas for answers. Miko (Kiki Sukezane) continues her rescue mission and travels in search of her sword. Elsewhere, Tommy (Robbie Kay) must use his ability to save the life of someone close to him.

Meanwhile, Luke (Zachary Levi) comes up against unexpected obstacles in his relationship with his wife, Joanne (Judi Shekoni), while Carlos (Ryan Guzman) takes major steps forward in his heroic journey.
name: The Needs of the Many

description:
Noah Bennet (Jack Coleman) and Quentin (Henry Zebrowski) take on Renautas while Miko's plan to retrieve her sword may land her in trouble. Malina's (Danika Yarosh) journey bring her closer to the truth. Elsewhere, Luke (Zachary Levi) returns home to confront his past and the authorities close in on Tommy (Robbie Kay).

Meanwhile, Carlos (Ryan Guzman) may have found an unexpected ally and Erica (Rya Khilstedt) solidifies her plans.
name: The Lion's Den

description: Jay Garrick (guest star Teddy Sears), a mysterious man from Earth-2, appears at S.T.A.R. Labs with a dire warning about an evil speedster named Zoom, who is set on destroying The Flash. Barry (Grant Gustin) and the team must decide if they can trust this stranger even as they face yet another powerful meta-human. Meanwhile, Joe (Jesse L. Martin) must deal with a determined officer named Patty Spivot (guest star Shantel VanSanten) who wants to join his meta-human task force.
name: Flash of Two Worlds

has_staff_review.name: The Flash Episode 202: "Flash of Two Worlds"

deck: Oliver is doubly concerned after family friend Jessica Danforth annouces her candidacy for mayor
description:
When an old family friend, Jessica Danforth (guest-star Jeri Ryan), tells Oliver (Stephen Amell) and Thea (Willa Holland) that she is going to run for mayor, both Queens are concerned considering the last three mayors have been murdered. Despite their protests, Jessica makes her announcement so the Green Arrow and Speedy vow to protect her.

Meanwhile, Thea begins to exhibit effects from the Lazarus Pit. In addition, Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) is faced with a tough business decision and looks to one of her employees, Curtis Holt (guest-star Echo Kellum), for help.
name: The Candidate

description: The Guardians crash land on a space station run by the Grandmaster, who schemes to get Drax back in the gladiatorial arena to battle his ultimate opponent: Gamora.
name: Take The Milano and Run

description:
The Gang climb aboard the cruise ship run by Fred's cousin, despite Velma's strong dislike of water. But a water phobia is the least of their problems when a terrifying Sea Monster attacks the ship!

Velma's fear of water is put to the test when the gang goes aboard a cruise ship run by Fred's cousin. And to make things worse - a sea monster appears.
name: All Paws On Deck

description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn.
name: Back to the Barn

description:
It's Scooby's dream come true as the gang visits the set of his favorite TV show and he meets the star, his celebrity crush, a dog actress who plays a detective on the screen. Now all Scooby has to do is work up the courage to actually talk to her while also solving the mystery of the monstrous Gargoyle attacking the production!

Scooby gets to visit the set of his favorite TV show and meet his favorite actress.
name: Poodle Justice

description: On a remote Army outpost, a fearsome alien warlord the Fisher King sets in motion a twisted plan to ensure his own survival. The ripples will be felt around the universe. Is this chain of events inevitable? And can the Doctor do the unthinkable?
name: Before the Flood

description: Captain Barnes (Michael Chiklis) is called to duty to create a law-abiding task force, with the help of Gordon. Meanwhile, Penguin gets caught up in a favor for Galavan, and Nygma asks Kringle out on a date.
name: Strike Force

series.name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic

description: Shaggy takes the Gang to the Minor League Baseball stadium of his youth only to learn that it's about to be shut down because a Ghostly Baseball Player is scaring away the fans - and the team! Shaggy puts aside his cowardly ways to saves his home team but will Scooby stand by his, now not so scared, pal?
name: Grand Scam

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hatashite hontni kore de owaru no ka wa wareware ni mo mada wakaranai)

After many battles, the party's journey has reached its end. As the climax approaches, the heroes are confronted by a flood of tropes and cliches. Of course, the sexy scenes are at their climax too!
name: No One Knows The End

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (J Ni Gt Haruki to Shimai-tachi no Kizuna)

The sisters get unusual close.
name: Building Twelve: The Bond Between Haruki & His Sisters

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ore no Kokoro)

True love.
name: My Heart

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Guddo Mningu Purizun)

Hana continues pressing Kiyoshi in order to exact her revenge, but Kiyoshi employs an adaptation of a classical military strategy to counter her. Once all the boys are locked into their cells for the night, will they be able to complete their plan?
name: Good Morning, Prison!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Iri Gin'nan)

Wakako eats roasted gingko nuts.
name: Roasted Ginkgo Nuts

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hatenaki Kya)

Yukihira is a popular neighborhood restaurant where Yukihira Soma helps out in the hopes of surpassing his father as a chef one day. But land sharks are after their restaurant, and one day Soma tells them that the restaurant will close if they couldn't serve satisfactory food to their customers. The land sharks are only too happy to sabotage the restaurant's fridge and gleefully orders Soma to serve them a meat dish...
name: An Endless Wasteland

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kami no Shita)

Under his father's orders, Soma attempts to transfer into one of Japan's top culinary schools, Togetsu Tea House Culinary Academy. His examiner, Nakiri Erina, is a student said to possess humanity's best palate: the God Tongue.
name: God Tongue

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kono Ryrijin wa Warawanai)

Just barely squeaking past the academy's transfer exam, Soma causes and uproar at the opening ceremony by making a brash speech in front of the entire class. In his very first class, he's paired with Tadokoro Megumi, a girl who is at risk of expulsion and is intent on keeping a low profile in order to survive.
name: That Chef Never Smiles

description:
Proper Japanese Title: () (Kyokusei no Maria)

Soma arrives at Polar Star Dormitory with high expectations, only to find it a creepy, run-down place. He is then informed by the dorm warden, Daimido Fumio, that he can only live at the dorm after he impresses her with his cooking. Soma rises up to the challenge!
name: The Madonna of the Polar Star

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kri no Jo to Haru no Arashi)

Isshiki Satoshi is the only second-year from the high school division in Polar Bear Dormitory. Full of ambition to join the Elite Ten, Soma challenges Isshiki right away, but he learns there are many rules that must be met in order for a formal challenge to occur...
name: The Ice Queen and the Spring Storm

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Niku no Shinryakusha)

Soma is drawn to Donmono Research Society, one of the academy's many cooking clubs, and takes Megumi with him to check it out. But they only find the club leader, Konishi, who's distraught over his club's imminent demise at the hands of Erina.
name: The Meat Invader

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ( (Shizukanaru Donburi, Yben'na Donburi)

The Shokugeki between Mito Ikumi and Yukihira Soma has begun! Everyone, including Erina, is convinced that Ikumi, the Meat Master, will win. Soma, on the other hand, is greeted by jeers the moment he enters the arena. Will Soma be able to save Don RS?
name: The Quiet Don, The Eloquent Don

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hass to Sz no Kyskyoku)

The training camp is considered the first trial by fire for students in Totsuki's high school division. Dozens of students are said to be expelled and sent away every day, and the number of students is said to be reduced below half by the camp's end. Intent on survival, Soma and his friends embark on their journey to the hellish camp in one of Totsuki Resorts' hotels.
name: The Concerto of Inspiration and Imagination

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yama o Irodoru i)

Inui Hinako, a Totsuki alumna, has tasked Soma's group with making a Japanese dish using available ingredients in the area. Anything other than condiments and spices must be procured from their immediate environs. Soma, provoked by Takumi Aldini's challenge, has a flash of inspiration and dashes out with Megumi to find ingredients for their dish!
name: The Breading to Adorn the Mountains

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Shij no Rusetto)

The Polar Star members have managed to survive the first day of camp. Megumi starts to build some confidence by successfully supporting Soma. But now, she and Soma have to face the second day with a genius of French cuisine, Shinomiya, who'd already expelled more than 30 students the day prior...
name: The Heavenly Recette

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Higashi-kara Kita Majutsushi)

Soma recklessly challenges Shinomiya to a Shokugeki in order to have him retract his decision to expel Megumi. Shinomiya refuses, but Dojima half forces him to accept. However, Dojima also imposes a condition on Soma and Megumi--Megumi must be the main chef! If they lose, Soma will also be expelled. The unofficial Shokougeki is about to begin!
name: The Magician from the East

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hito Sara no Kioku)

The unofficial Shokugeki between Shinomiya and the Megumi-Soma pair has begun. With expulsion on the line, the judging is underway. Megumi's first dish as the main chef is her own take on the nine-vegetable terrine Shinomiya assigned--the Rainbow Terrine, made from seven types of vegetables!
name: The Memory of a Dish

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yoake Mae no Tamago-tachi)

Third night of camp. Soma and the others manage to make it through their arduous trials. But now they're given a new trial for the next morning: to come up with a menu item that uses eggs.
name: Eggs Before Dawn

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Metamorufze)

The students have been tasked with creating an egg-based breakfast menu item for a buffet, and they must persuade guests to consume 200 servings before two hours' time. Soma's souffle omelets keep deflating before the guests have a chance to take the dish. With only 30 minutes remaining, Soma has served less than 10 guests--with defeat imminent, Soma recalls Joichiro's advice and decides to make a last-ditch effort to make a comeback!
name: Metamorphosis

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Syra to Yobareda Otoko)

With the camp over, surviving students return to Totsuki Academy. Soma manages to miss his bus, but so does Erina, so they end up going back on the same car. As awkward conversation ensues, Soma learns from Erina that the Autumn Elections are coming...
name: The Man Called the Demon

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Manri o Kakeru Ryrinin)

When Soma's father, Joichiro, suddenly shows up on Polar Star Dormitory's doorstep, Soma finds out that his father was an alum of Totsuki Academy and Polar Star Dormitory. Joichiro challenges Soma to a cooking duel to find out how far his son has come. How will the family duel end?
name: The Chef Who's Crossed a Thousand Leagues

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kann no Karaage)

Soma goes back home for the first time in a long while over an extended break. Stormed by people who were waiting for Yukihira to reopen, Soma decides to serve his customers. But among them are the leaders of the shopping district, who tell Soma that the shopping district is on its last breath as a new shopping complex at the train station steals all of their customers...
name: The Seductive Karaage

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Seishun no Karaage)

Home to Diner Yukihira, Sumire Avenue Shopping District is on its last legs after the karaage specialty store, Mozuya, has taken all their customers. Soma recruits Kurase and Nikumi to help devise a plan to recoup customers: the Walk-n-Eat Karaage. The summer karaage campaign is about to begin!
name: The Karaage of Youth

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Erabareshi Mono)

As the first semester draws to a close, the names of students who'll participate in the Autumn Elections are posted in Totsuki Academy. The assigned topic is a curry dish, leading Soma to seek out a certain alumna Joichiro told him about.
name: The Chosen One

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 440kcal (Nebare, Natt Okura Don Bukkake Chzu Toppingu Bent Yonhyakuyonj Kiro Karor)

Feeding yourself isn't easy on a fixed budget in boarding school. Yo Sato learns it's even harder when brawls break out every night at local supermarkets the moment bento meals go on sale. The only way to get a bento is to fight the wolves for one.
name: Stick with It, Natto Okra Rice Bowl with Cheese Topping Bento 440kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 674kcal (Saba no Misoni Bent Roppyakunanajyon Kiro Karor)

Yo and Hana join the Half-Pricers Club. Its leader, Sen, teaches them the ropes, then sends them out into the wild to fend for themselves. There's a lot to learn, but it looks like Yo might turn out to be a successful wolf after all.
name: Mackerel Boiled in Miso Bento 674kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 1080kcal (mori Chzu Katsu Kar Senhachij Kiro Karor)

The kendo club at school has their own ideas about how to acquire half-price bentos, and its captain makes a tempting offer to entice Yo into their fold. The time has come for Yo to ask himself what his motivation is for being a wolf.
name: Large Cheese Pork Cutlet Curry Rice 1080kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 852kcal (Butaniku Shgayaki Bent Happyakugojni Kiro Karor)

It's nothing but trouble when Yo's half-Italian cousin Ayame shows up and starts causing problems. Meanwhile, some shadowy organization appears to be gathering information about the local wolves.
name: Ginger Fried Pork Bento 852kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 326kcal (Hokkaid no Shake o Tsukatta Arajiru Sanbyakunijroku Kiro Karor)

Yo inadvertently finds himself caught up in a brewing turf war between wolves from the east and west sides of town. Wolves generally do their own thing, but this time they might need to work together to defend what belongs to them.
name: Hokkaido Salmon Fish Soup 326kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 795kcal (Tokusei Zangi Bent Nanahyakukyjgo Kiro Karor)

The Monarch, leader of the eastern wolves, claims he wants to take over the supermarkets in the west as well. Sen comes up with a plan to foil him, while Ayame learns there might be more going on here than meets the eye.
name: Special Hokkaido Style Fried Chicken Bento 795kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 752kcal 1100kcal (Omuppai Bent Nanahyakugojni Kiro Karor to Rokomokkori Bent Senhyaku Kiro Karor)

The Half-Pricers Club gets free tickets to a Hawaii-themed water park, so it's excursion time! While there, Yo learns that supermarkets aren't the only places where bento brawls occur.
name: Bosomelet Bento 752kcal and Loco Moco Bulging Bento 1100kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 765kcal (Tappuri Nira Hanbgu Bent Nanahyakurokujgo Kiro Karor)

An unfortunate mishap lands Yo in the hospital. Twin sisters Kyo and Kyo, student council officers from Ayame's school, are trying to learn more about Sen. When they mistake Yo, covered in bandages, for Sen, a comedy of errors ensues.
name: Hamburg Steak Loaded with Garlic Chives Bento 765kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 2910kcal340kcal (Seiy Waf Makunouchi Tsumeawase J Nisenkyhyakuj Kiro Karor to Hokkori Okayu Bent Sanbyakuyonj Kiro Karor)

Homemade bentos are the order of the day, but sometimes these can prove just as dangerous as bentos won in battle. Asebi believes Yo is a big fan of her cooking, while Ume decides to take things up a notch with Hana.
name: Deluxe Western and Japanese Food Assortment 2910kcal and Piping Hot Porridge Bento 340kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 480kcal (Sore wa Mukashi Sobo no Ie de Tabeta Atataka de Yasashii Ajiwai. Kokoro nimo Karada nimo Yasashii Wa no Ryri. Ume to Chirimenjako Gohan to Kisetsu no Yasai Tappuri no Nimono Bent Yonhyakuhachij Kiro Karor)

There's a new wolf duo in town, and they go by the name Orthros. This pair seems to be as unbeatable as they are mysterious, but the real surprise comes when it's revealed that their true identities aren't so shrouded in mystery after all.
name: A Warm, Gentle Flavor I Remember from Long Ago at My Grandmother's House. A Japanese Dish Easy on Both Mind and Body. Plum and Dried Sardines over Rice with Plenty of Stewed Seasonal Vegetables Bento 480kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 125kcal (Pokari Suetto Hyakunijgo Kiro Karor)

A certain supermarket puts fresh eel bentos on sale one day each summer, and this is sure to attract plenty of wolves. But to make it there, first Sen will have to recover from a cold, and Orthros will have to overcome the specter of their painful past.
name: Pocari Sweat 125kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 790kcal (Kokusan Unagi Bent Nanahyakukyj Kiro Karor)

The old nemesis of Orthros shows up in town to undermine them once again. With Sen still sick with a cold, it will be up to Yo to figure out a way to rebalance the playing field for all the wolves, as they vie for seasonal eel bentos.
name: Domestic Eel Bento 790kcal

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ten o chiginda hi)

Takerus first day at the Tenbi Academy is full of fights and panties. After accidentally kissing a second-year girl, she challenges him to a duel in front of the entire student body. Without a Maken or Element, how is he supposed to protect himself?
name: The Day We Swore to Heaven

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Onnanoko wa Sugoin desu)

The beginning of the school year could only mean one thing: time for physical exams! But after getting caught peeking in on the girls from his class, Takeru finds out that hes an anomaly at Tenbi, and that no Maken can be matched to him.
name: Girls Are Amazing

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (MAKENKI e Ykoso)

Takeru decides to join the Security Committee! To welcome its new members, the Committee takes a trip to the hot springs. Things are going well until a bear shows up, giving the girls the Tenbi Academy a chance to show off their special powers.
name: Welcome to Maken-ki

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Teki wa Tenbi ni Ari)

Himegami asks Takeru to go on a shopping date?! Of course, she has an ulterior motive: to inspect the mysterious mark on Takerus chest. Sounds easy enough, but her plans are interrupted by her roommates, her fan club, and an unknown stalker.
name: The Enemy Is at Tenbi

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Tenbi Saiky no Onna)

Its time for the clubs at Tenbi to negotiate their annual budgets! Takeru and Uru try to work together to help the Security Committee, but their work is interrupted by an assailant who claims to be responsible for the random acts of violence on campus.
name: The Strongest Girl in Tenbi

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Tenbi ni Ame no Kudaru Gotoku)

Since Takeru's first day at Tenbi, Inaho has called him her fianc. On a rainy night, the story of their past together is revealed, and Takeru's Elemental powers surface in order to protect his friend (and an adorable new addition to the household).
name: Like Rain on a Sunny Day

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Tenbi no Orita Megamitachi)

A group of beautiful, powerful transfer students arrive at Tenbi in order to root out a mysterious secret society. But before they can get to work, theyll have to prove their strength against the girls of Makenki in an epic volleyball showdown.
name: The Goddesses Who Came Down to Tenbi

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Shiria no Subete o Agechaimasu)

Syria is Tenbi's newest transfer student, and she's taken quite an interest in Takeru! What does she plan to do with him in the disused shack on the outskirts of campus?!
name: Syria Will Give You Everything

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Arashi o Yobu Suijbasen)

The boys of Tenbi Academy petition the faculty for co-ed swim classes (for the sake of gender equality, of course). Naturally, the girls protest. There's only one way to solve this dilemma: a boys-versus-girls water fight full of swimsuits and nosebleeds!
name: Stormy Games

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hikari to Kage no Shjo)

If Takeru fails his Element practical again, he'll be kicked out of Makenki! Meanwhile, there's something not quite right about Minerva, the newest member of Venus to transfer to Tenbi. Why is she confronting Himegami in the woods?
name: The Girls of Light and Shadow

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Macaron Gentai Service Day)

Takeru gets a Maken! The secret history of Makenki! A dangerous new threat! But most important, the girls of the Security Committee don their skimpiest outfits and get jobs at the local maid caf in order to pay for their bikini-filled summer camp.
name: Macaron Limited-Time Only Service Day

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Rakuen o Mamorumono)

Kamigari kidnaps Haruko as part of an incomprehensible evil scheme concerning Takeru's untapped powers. When things backfire and Takeru goes out of control, only one person can stop him from destroying Tenbi Academy.
name: Protectors of Paradise

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ? (Natsu Da! Mizugi Da! Gasshuku Da!)

Takeru and the rest of the gang head to the beach for some serious training, so you know what that means: tiny swimsuits, a giant octopus attack, and one promiscuous sleep-groper!
name: OVA: It's Summer! It's Swimsuits! It's Training Camp!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Shibusen, Nygaku!)

When 14-year-old middle-schooler Tsugumi Harudori discovers she is a weapon, she flies to America to enroll at DWMA. There, she meets the absent-minded Meme Tatane and the patrician Anya Hepburn, both of whom are meisters that are also new enrollees.
name: Enrolling at DWMA!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ! (Joshi Ry a ra Karuto!)

Fellow student Eternal Feather shows Tsugumi, Meme and Anya around the girls' dorm, and they meet some of the residents there. By the next morning, all three had lost their allowance, and thus had to take part-time jobs at a caf named "Deathbucks."
name: Girls' Dorms  la Carte!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ! (Joshi Ry no Majo!)

Eternal Feather reveals more about Kim's history, as well as the origin of her name. A new threat, known as "Traitor," menaces the students of DWMA, and Sid sends Clay and Akane to scare them off. Anya feels left out when she misses her turn with Tsugumi.
name: The Witch of the Girls' Dorm!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: , ! (Mayotte, Hashitte!)

After a nightmare, Tsugumi wonders why the meisters choose to come to DWMA. She spends some time talking to Akane, who asks her to be his girlfriend, only to say he was joking. The class takes their physical fitness exams, where both Meme and Anya excel.
name: Waver, Run!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ! (Osasoi Faitingu!)

After dreaming about Kim, Jacqueline is bothered by feelings of attraction for her. Kim leads the girls in a pool-cleaning job, and after she takes most of the pay, they help Jacqueline try to win Kim over, while learning about her mysterious background.
name: Invitation Fighting!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ! (Koko wa Riaru Faito!)

Liz and Patty Thompson take jobs as waitresses at Deathbucks, and manage to scare off much of the clientele, including Meme and Anya. However, Tsugumi sees something in them, and fights to keep going to the caf, determined to become more like them.
name: This Is a Real Fight!
